<subSubSection id="6878A4630D3B35554EC4D4C54511EB38" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="description">
<paragraph id="618C1165FD31C7D76A33C1614416A70D" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Additional description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7965C89E5CE5EE26ABDB11E3A1305389" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
This species is variable in its pronotal color (
<bibRefCitation id="C507849D9E2FEB305E642E6B91B8ED81" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2359.1.1" author="Gerstmeier, R" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="1 - 34" refId="B5" refString="Gerstmeier, R, Bernhard, N, 2010. Revision of the genus Tillicera Spinola, 1841 (Coleoptera: Cleridae, Clerinae). Zootaxa 2359 (1): 1 - 34, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2359.1.1" title="Revision of the genus Tillicera Spinola, 1841 (Coleoptera: Cleridae, Clerinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2359.1.1" volume="2359" year="2010">Gerstmeier and Bernhard 2010</bibRefCitation>
). Additional variation is recognized as follows: head and pronotum completely reddish (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E5EBD28E47512F1C7EE97BF3CDDC2B61" captionStart="Figures 1–12" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 12. Habitus of Tillicera species 1 Tillicera auratofasciata 2 T. aurivillosa 3 T. bibalteata 4 T. callosa 5, 6 T. cleroides 7, 8 T. hirsuta 9, 10 T. ihlei 11, 12 T. javana. Scale bars 2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.80097.figures1-12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672265" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">11</figureCitation>
); legs yellowish (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3CCF4A640A5C8C85F168865B8890E9FC" captionStart="Figures 1–12" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 12. Habitus of Tillicera species 1 Tillicera auratofasciata 2 T. aurivillosa 3 T. bibalteata 4 T. callosa 5, 6 T. cleroides 7, 8 T. hirsuta 9, 10 T. ihlei 11, 12 T. javana. Scale bars 2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.80097.figures1-12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672265" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">12</figureCitation>
). Antennomeres V-X vestigial with an area vested with sensilla basiconica at apical margin in ventral view; male XI of dorsal surface with pit-like sensillum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9DA729D2570AE43A5830ECAE3DEC2249" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="remarks">
