<taxonomicName id="BBDE1B23EE702522B7B908188F16F408" class="Insecta" genus="T." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="T. javana" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="javana">
<emphasis id="DAFB5BF7217ACB31680DC2EB99423A6A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">T. javana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, used to illustrate a likeness to mutilid wasps, appears to be a misidentified specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="17133F332D09AAB59BC342B5A525E47A" authority="Spinola, 1841" authorityName="Gerstmeier &amp; Bernhard" authorityYear="2010" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Tillicera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tillicera tonkinensis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tonkinensis">
<emphasis id="F718029FCE964FBDC10E8DE9F7534C8F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Tillicera tonkinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Gerstmeier &amp; Bernhard, 2010
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
